column12:
What Am I Looking At?
'Hard' scores are the the three subcategories of switch scoring that focus on the intrinsic, physical performance characteristics of switches - Push Feel, Wobble, and Sound. These comprise a total of 70 of the 100 points used in my switch scoring system and are not subject to the time decay as seen in the Overall and Soft total tabs.
